{
  "stem": "21310.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I was trying to type.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I taught myself how to type.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Wasn't touch-typing, it was just with two fingers.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But shorthand and typing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Well, again, and that-- the order was given already in, I think, was October or November of 1939 that all Jews had to wear white armband with a blue Mogen David.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And this was for means of identification.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So naturally, and-- and, you know, punishment for being caught without it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And again, people were standing in line for bread, for instance.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And any hoodlum could come, and if you were closer to the store for bread, they could chase you out.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "You, Jew, go in the end of the line.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "These same people would be caught in the street for some labor.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "The Germans really had a ball with the Orthodox Jews.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "You know, they wore their special garbs and had the beard.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "So frequently, you could see that they were pulling on their beards and making them cut-- cutting their beards.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I saw, at one point, where a German officer was standing there and made an old Jew lie down on the floor and lick his boots.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "You had to get off the sidewalk when you saw a German.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And men had to take their hats off.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And sometimes when you got off the sidewalk and you looked in the German's face, you could get beaten up, you know, with the remark, how dare you look in my face.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And when you learned your lesson and the next time you went into the-- got off the sidewalk and didn't look, so, what's wrong with you?",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Why don't you-- why can't you look into-- into my eyes?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And get beaten up for that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Naturally, the bank accounts were frozen.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
